---
title: `$h_t_t_p::is()`
description: Detect current request type.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
HTTP::is($id = null, $key = null);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
if (HTTP::is('post')) {
    // Is a `POST` request!
}
~~~

~~~ .php
if (HTTP::is('post', 'time')) {
    // Is has `time` key in `$_POST` array either it contains a value or not
    // This is equal to `if (array_key_exists('time', $_POST ?? [])) {}`
}

if (HTTP::post('time')) {
    // Is has `time` key in `$_POST` array and it contains a value
    // This is equal to `if (!empty($_POST['time']) || empty($_POST['time']) && $_POST['time'] === 0 || $_POST['time'] === '0') {}`
}
~~~